 shows their complementary powers. Recurring themes link each chapter, throwing a powerful light on aesthetic encounters by foregrounding such pivotal notions as play, fundedness and the role of memory, the defining quality of an artwork, energies of objects, potencies, rhythm, form, presentational abstraction, medium, symbolization, intuition, role of the body, and the non-argumentative nature of art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aAesthetics. 0aArtxPhilosophy. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Art Theory. 4aLiterature : Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Aesthetics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848826440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438488264423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438488264/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles